- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the functionality of a computer algebra package for symbolic manipulation of nested sums and iterated integrals. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper deals with the manipulation of mathematical expressions and functions, which is relevant to control theory and system analysis. 
- cs.CA (Computational Geometry) is a possible category as the paper deals with the computation of nested sums and integrals, which can be relevant to computational geometry. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper may discuss algorithms and data structures used in the implementation of the HarmonicSums package. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the logical foundations of the HarmonicSums package and its algorithms.
